<subSubSection id="DB9B69A0431C8F53496EFFC6C0DE3F12" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="100125D053715DCCFAD3B798348FE829" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F32E46D0DCCE7C6E0DDD676EF1331E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="482B8C7DA5232EB80A645D557295D8A7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="F." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="F. faberi" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="faberi">
<emphasis id="EB745B2CBFCCE4A8284E1A666AC77523" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">F. faberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having erect stems, membranous leaf blades, and oblong petals, but differs by the terete (vs. quadrangular) stems, densely puberulous (vs. green and glabrous or shortly setose near leaf blade base) petioles, and elliptic (vs. broadly lanceolate, oblong, ovate, or rarely lanceolate) leaf blades.
</paragraph>
<caption id="22B878FF69BD41DEF0415CBED789FFAA" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.197.82670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688531" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
